---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { AUTHOR, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`CV · ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={`CV of ${AUTHOR.name}.`} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<header class="cv-head">
				<h1>{AUTHOR.name}</h1>
				<p>
					{AUTHOR.email} · <a href={AUTHOR.github}>GitHub</a> ·
					<a href={AUTHOR.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a> ·
					<a href="/cv.pdf">PDF</a>
				</p>
			</header>

			<section>
				<h2>Summary</h2>
				<p>
					Distributed systems / infra engineer working on latency-sensitive realtime ML
					inference at LinkedIn ads scale — high-QPS GPU serving, embedding pipelines,
					and entity-cache infrastructure in scope. Going deep on LLM inference serving
					as the next step: paged attention, continuous batching, disaggregated
					prefill/decode.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Experience</h2>
				<article>
					<h3>
						LinkedIn <span class="muted">· Ads Serving Infra · Apr 2019 – present</span>
					</h3>
					<p class="muted">
						Senior Software Engineer (Mar 2021 – present) ·
						Software Engineer (Apr 2019 – Mar 2021)
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>
							Designed and shipped dual-fire serving (<a href="/projects#differential-serving">differential serving</a>)
							that scores live ad-ranking requests on a TensorFlow CPU champion and a
							PyTorch GPU candidate in parallel, with async overlap, three-gate routing
							(experiment / tmax / config kill switch), and asymmetric resolution —
							A/B-ing a new GPU inference stack at request granularity without regressing
							the served path. Authored the RFC; owned the serving-side integration end
							to end (6 PRs); ~400 QPS sustainable per A100 under a 50ms GPU
							round-trip budget. <span class="muted">(2026)</span>
						</li>
						<li>
							Co-designed the infra for collapsing retrieval and first-pass ranking into
							a single <a href="/projects#early-stage-ranking">Two-Tower scoring layer</a>
							over ~10M creatives, with nearline embedding generation, member-vs-creative
							version alignment via a model-registry source of truth, and per-shard
							dot-product scoring on the indexer fleet. Authored the MS1 RFC for the
							embedding pipeline; first end-to-end BST delivered an over-20% onsite
							CTR lift. <span class="muted">(2025–2026)</span>
						</li>
						<li>
							Lead-authored the RFCs and rollout that moved hundreds of ads-serving
							hosts off direct Oracle reads onto a per-account-partitioned Kafka +
							Couchbase pipeline (<a href="/projects#entity-cache-rewrite">tscp-cache NextGen</a>),
							with a multi-version state machine, validator-driven reconciliation, and a
							low-latency shortcut path for inactivation signals. Decoupled the in-memory
							cache from the indexer and shipped a portable cache library reused by
							adjacent ads services. <span class="muted">(2021)</span>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</article>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Open source</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>[repo-name] — one-line description, with star count if interesting.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Education</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>Rice University</strong>, Houston, TX — Master of Computer Science
					<span class="muted">· Aug 2017 – Dec 2018</span>
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Wuhan University</strong>, Wuhan, China — Bachelor of Software Engineering
					<span class="muted">· Sep 2013 – Jun 2017</span>
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.cv-head {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	.muted {
		color: #888;
		font-weight: normal;
	}
	section {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}
	article {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	h3 {
		margin-bottom: 0.25em;
	}
</style>
